<TEXT>
Death plot
PHNOM PENH: Cambodian police have arrested three farmers on charges of
conspiring to abduct or kill foreigners for cash rewards from the Khmer Rouge.
The Cambodia Daily said the three, who had confessed, were arrested in the
northwest city of Battambang.
</TEXT>
