<DOCNO>GH951207-000033</DOCNO>
<DOCID>GH951207-000033</DOCID>
<DATE>951207</DATE>
<HEADLINE>Remand in murder inquiry</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>1</EDITION>
<PAGE>3</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>975011878</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
A MAN appeared in private at Greenock Sheriff Court yesterday, charged with the
murder of a man whose body has not been found.
Mr James Cummings, 28, c/o Angus Road, Greenock, made no plea or declaration
and the case was continued for further inquiries.
He is charged with the murder of a 21-year-old Glasgow man, Roderick Campbell,
in a house in Greenock. Further details were not released.
Mr Campbell, of Gladsmuir Road, Hillington, disappeared about two weeks ago. A
week later, police launched an appeal for help saying they were becoming
increasingly concerned about him. Inquiries later switched from Glasgow to
Greenock and an investigation was launched in the Greenock area headed by
Detective Chief Inspector John Sherry.
Mr Cummings was remanded in custody after a brief appearance before Sheriff
George Crozier.
</TEXT>
