<HEADLINE>Russian plane goes missing</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>3</EDITION>
<PAGE>8</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>975011882</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
Moscow
A RUSSIAN plane with 96 people on board went missing in the Far East today and
is feared to have crashed, an Emergencies Ministry spokeswoman said.
The Tu-154 craft lost radio contact between Yuzhno-Sakhalinsk on the island of
Sakhalin and the eastern town of Khabarovsk. It was presumed the plane had
crashed.
The crash came a day after 49 people were killed and 33 injured in another
plane crash in Azerbaijan. A twin-engined Tu-134 went down shortly after
take-off.-Reuter
</TEXT>
