<TEXT>
STRATHCLYDE's education committee yesterday agreed to issue a consultative
document on a proposal to close Glasgow's Garthamlock secondary.
Councillors will consider the situation and look at a series of options on
closure when the consultation exercise ends on February 2.
Parents have been considering using the Government's opting-out legislation as
a means of saving the school.
