<HEADLINE>Untouched</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>3</EDITION>
<PAGE>16</PAGE>
<ARTICLETYPE>Correspondence</ARTICLETYPE>
<RECORDNO>975011890</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
I was disgusted at the David Bowie concert at the SECC (November 30). On
arrival we were informed that Morrisey was ill and I can only think that this
was due to him having a preview of the show as it was dire. Flashing lights,
incoherent ramblings, and weird electronics did nothing for me. David Bowie
should retire perhaps. I should have taken the refund and bought tickets for
Rod Stewart.
Neil Stewart,
61 Dunmore Street, Balfron.
</TEXT>
