<TEXT>
IN the second match of last night's Under-21 Inter-District Championship double
header at Murrayfield, Scottish Exiles, playing a conservative game, defeated
Edinburgh 19-17. Fourteen of the Exiles' points came from their stand off and
captain Jamie McKee from four penalties and the conversion of a first half try
