<TEXT>
GLASGOW achieved their second victory in the Scottish Under-21 Inter-District
Championship with a 22-17 win over North and Midlands at Murrayfield last
night. writes Alan Lorimer.
North and Midlands, with a much improved performance from their first round
effort against Edinburgh, should have made more of their greater territorial
gains.
Their hard working pack, in which Aberdeen University's Fraser Wilson at lock
and Gregor Hayter of Dundee High School FP at No.8 were impressive, had the
better of the forward exchanges, but Glasgow, much the sharper behind the
scrum, made their pace tell to produce two tries by wingers Geoff Caldwell and
Colin McRobert to follow up an early score by flanker Rob Wylie.
Glasgow's other points came from two conversions and one penalty by West of
Scotland full back Tony Greenshields.
For North and Midlands, Jon Goldie, who had a useful outing on the right wing,
and Hayter crossed for tries while stand-off Gerry Tosh kicked two conversions
and one penalty goal.
