<DOCNO>GH951207-000064</DOCNO>
<DOCID>GH951207-000064</DOCID>
<DATE>951207</DATE>
<HEADLINE>Carlton continues to perform well</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>CHRISTOPHER SIMS</BYLINE>
<EDITION>1</EDITION>
<PAGE>21</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>975011911</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
TELEVISION broadcaster and programme maker Carlton Communications is
maintaining its strong growth trend with another good set of results for the
year to September.
Profits rose 30% to #246.7m and earnings per share were 21% ahead at 65.3p.
Dividends are raised 14% to 23.6p. Year-end net cash stood at #90.6m.
Carlton holds the London weekday and Midlands ITV licences following its
purchase of Central, which is now fully integrated and yielding the cost
savings expected. The group is also a major producer of programmes for the
whole network, spending #160m a year on new work. Successful series include
Inspector Morse, Soldier, Soldier and Peak Practice. Its library of programmes
is also building up rapidly.
Broadcast television overall raised operating profits by 71% to #123m helped by
a full contribution from Central. Carlton claims to be increasing its share of
television advertising. The other strong performer was video and sound products
where profits rose 43% to #32.5m.
Video production and distribution saw a 4% dip to #60.7m, due to continuing
losses in Carlton Home Entertainment, which makes and distributes video and
music compilations, and lower margins on video cassette production. Home
entertainment has been reorganised but it will take time to realise the
benefits.
The main business of the division is the manufacture and distribution of
pre-recorded cassettes by the Technicolor subsidiary for the video retail
market. The video recorder population in the US and Europe is projected to grow
at 3% a year. Titles processed included The Lion King which sold 28 million
copies. Capacity was increased and production speeded up to meet demand.
The fourth division, film and television services, made 9% more at #41.6m.
Carlton shares closed 3p firmer at 1003p.
FACT FILE
Full year 1995 1994
Turnover #1600m #1400
Pre-tax profits #247m #190m
EPS 60p 50.5p
Dividend 23.6p 20.6p
</TEXT>
