<TEXT>
NORTHAMPTON half backs Paul Grayson and Matt Dawson will earn their first caps
when England play Western Samoa at Twickenham on December 16.
Kyran Bracken, scrum half against South Africa, is dropped to make way for
Dawson, while Mike Catt transfers from stand-off to full back - his position
last season - to the exclusion of Jonathan Callard. Also dropped are Bath
forwards Victor Ubogu and Andy Robinson.
Graham Rowntree comes into the front row at loose head prop, with Jason Leonard
switching to tight head.
Lawrence Dallaglio wins his first full cap at flanker.
Dawson and Grayson earned their call-ups with magnificent displays for the
Midlands in their 40-19 victory over the South Sea Islanders last weekend.
