<TEXT>
FOUR candidates are to be interviewed in Oban today for the Camanachd
Association's first full-time administrator's post. The short-leet, selected
from more than 50 applicants, was ratified at a special meeting in Fort William
earlier this week.
The candidates are the president of the Camanachd Association, Duncan Cameron
of Glasgow, the current part-time secretary/treasurer, Alastair MacIntyre of
Fort William, plus Colin Clark, a former bank manager from Oban who is
treasurer of Oban Camanachd, and Calum Smith, originally from Lewis, treasurer
of the Fort William club.
q THE Scottish Sports Council have recognised the contribution made to shinty
by Jack Richmond of Newtonmore. He is one of five leading figures whose
voluntary contribution to sport will be recognised tonight at an awards
ceremony at Murrayfield stadium in Edinburgh.
Cricket
FORMER internationalist Bobby Hill yesterday looked forward to his new role as
Scotland's chairman of selectors and admitted there is a lot of work to be
done. He was elected at the SCU's annual meeting in Perth, succeeding Hugh
Stevenson, who died in August.
The new chairman said: ``We've got one season to find the right blend for the
World Cup in Malaysia in 1997, so the players have everything to play for next
year. The door is open to anyone who can prove they're good enough to play for
Scotland.''
Financially the Union had a good year, with their income up by over #3200. The
net surplus compared with previous years advanced to #18,749.
Towards the close of the evening awards were made to George Strachan (West
Lothian County) as groundsman for the year and Edinburgh District as Area
champions, while the East and West Districts won the awards for the Under-19
and Under-16 District championships respectively.
Douglas Lockhard, winner of many awards this season, was the recipient of the
special award made by the President.
Squash
SCOTTISH champion Peter Nicol goes into today's final qualifying event, the
Mahindra International Challenge in India, virtually assured of a place in the
Hi-tech Super Series finals. With the top eight to qualify for the February
finals at a venue to be announced later this month, Nicol is in fifth place.
