<HEADLINE>ScotMet looks forward</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>1</EDITION>
<PAGE>19</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>975011942</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
SCOTTISH Metropolitan Property sees no upturn in the depressed UK property
market next year, but is confident that it will continue to thrive.
``We are in a strong position to take advantage of investment acquisition
opportunities,'' chairman David Walton told the company's annual meeting.
More than two thirds of ScotMet's property portfolio is in Scotland, where
property values have fared rather better than in England.
Mr Walton said the company had acquired #50m of new properties in Scotland and
the north of England since the spring, now some 20% of its portfolio.
Pre-tax profits, excluding gains and losses on asset sales, jumped 50.6% to
#8.7m in the year to August 15.
</TEXT>
