<HEADLINE>Two Scots events for women pros</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>BILL JOHNSON</BYLINE>
<EDITION>2</EDITION>
<PAGE>31</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>975011980</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
SCOTLAND will be hosting two tournaments on the American Express Tour, whose
1996 schedule was announced yesterday by chief executive Terry Coates.
McDonald's, who sponsor one of the four majors on the LPGA Tour in America,
will be backing the WPGA championship on August 8 to 11 at a Scottish course
still to be announced. It will be the first Tour event to be played solely for
charity with all proceeds going to the Ronald McDonald Children's Charities.
This is one of four new tournaments on the schedule of 20 events, an increase
of two from this season, while prize-money approaching #3m will be a record for
the Tour.
The only casualty is the Ford Classic after 14 years. This year at Chart Hills
in Kent it had prize-money of #110,000. Ford, however, will continue to sponsor
the Order of Merit.
Highlights of the season are the #500,000 Weetabix Women's British Open at
Woburn on August 15 to 18 and the Solheim Cup match against the Americans at St
Pierre, Chepstow, on September 20 to 22. The 1996 dates are:
May: 2-5 Welsh Open, St Pierre CC; 10-12 Costa Azul Open, Aroeria and Quinta do
Peru, near Lisbon; 24-26 Dutch Open TBA.
June: 7-9 Ford/Stimorol Danish Open, Vejle; 13-16 Deesse Swiss Open, Maison
Blanche, Geneva; 19-22 Evian Masters, Royal Golf Club Evian; 27-30 Austrian
Open, Vienna.
July: 4-7 Hennessy Cup, Refrath, Koln; 25-28 Guardian Irish Holidays Open,
Dublin.
August: 8-11 McDonald's WPGA Championship, TBA; 15-18 Weetabix Women's British
Open, Woburn; 22-25 Trygg Hansa Open; Haninge, Stockholm; Aug 29-Sept 1 The
Compaq Open, Orebro, Sweden.
Septemer: 20-22 Solheim Cup, St Pierre CC; 26-29 Maredo Open, Hotel
Treudelberg, Hamburg.
October: 3-6 Three Nations Cup, Henri-Chapelle, Belgium; 10-13 Italian Open di
Sicilia, Il Picciolo; 17-20 French Open, TBA; 24-27 Spanish Open, Hyatt La
Manga Club Resort.
Dates to be confirmed: Wilkinson Sword English Open, The Oxfordshire; Scottish
Open, Dalmahoy CC Resort.
</TEXT>
